<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-301-924  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 301 924.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Classroom Computer Learning  March 1989 v9 n6 p42(10).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Enter words and pictures the easy way - scan them. (buyers guide)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Olivas, Jerry.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Scanners are computer peripherals that allow users to capture textand graphics relatively quickly for subsequent processing andmanipulation.andP;  Scanners can be advantageous for schooladministrators, teachers and students.andP;  Image scanners digitizeimages in the form of on-off bits, then construct 'bit maps' ofimages.andP;  Optical character recognition (OCR) software is needed toconvert text images into ASCII code for subsequent processing.andO;Page scanners are suitable for desktop use and are priced frombelow $2,000.andP;  Hand scanners are smaller units that must be movedmanually across a page to scan desired material.andP;  Printer scannersenable printers to be turned into input devices by inserting anoptic sensing unit near the print head.andP;  Hand scanners and printerscanners are priced from below $1,000, but are less reliable andpowerful than larger scanners.andP;  In selecting a scanner, resolutionand gray shade detection capabilities, the unit's speed, and theunit's hardware requirements should be considered.andP;  A directory ofscanners costing less than $3,000 is provided, and includesmanufacturer data, compatible computer and software information,and summaries of product features.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     ScanningProductsDirectoriesEnd UsersFunctional CapabilitiesHardware Selection.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotographtable.andO;Caption:   Scanners for under $3,000. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>